    "body": "Nope, makes no difference.  \r\n\r\nI had another look via DevTools and see that the webview itself and the shadow root embedded object are resized and show the correct dimensions.  It is the content that hasn't also been redrawn  to reflect the resize.\r\n\r\nThere seems to be a few issues around webview and content redraws though nothing directly related.\r\n#6783 #7375 and others\r\n\r\nIn this case I just think a redraw should be forced on visibility and isn't.\r\n\r\nYou can see in the screenshot the selected webview element has correct size but content is old size when made hidden.\r\nI then resized container and made visible again.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"909\" alt=\"google chrome - github com - - screen shot 24-12-2016 2 16 22 pm\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1051701/21464520/483cf788-c9e4-11e6-8ce8-fc6096be29b8.png\">\r\n "
